[BUG] Connect-PnPOnline: Method not found: 'System.String System.String.Format(System.IFormatProvider, System.String, System. Object)'. ### Reporting an Issue or Missing Feature Unable to connect to SharePoint Online using Connect-PnPOnline. I can run this on my personal computer but am unable to do so on a Windows 2008 Server. I need to use local certificates, but I have also testet credentials and -Interactive with the same result. Also same result whether I run in x86 or x64. ### Expected behavior Connect to a specific SP site ### Actual behavior From Get-PnPException: ``` powershell Message : Method not found: 'System.String System.String.Format(System.IFormatProvider, System.String, System. Object)'. Stacktrace : at Microsoft.Identity.Client.AuthorityInfo..ctor(AuthorityType authorityType, String authority, B oolean validateAuthority) at Microsoft.Identity.Client.AbstractApplicationBuilder`1.WithAuthority(String authorityUri, Bool ean validateAuthority) at PnP.Framework.AuthenticationManager..ctor(String clientId, String redirectUrl, String tenantId , AzureEnvironment azureEnvironment, Action`1 tokenCacheCallback, ICustomWebUi customWebUi) at PnP.Framework.AuthenticationManager.CreateWithInteractiveLogin(String clientId, Action`2 openB rowserCallback, String tenantId, String successMessageHtml, String failureMessageHtml, AzureEnvironm ent azureEnvironment, Action`1 tokenCacheCallback) at PnP.PowerShell.Commands.Base.PnPConnectionHelper.InstantiateInteractiveConnection(Uri uri, Str ing clientId, String tenantAdminUrl, Boolean launchBrowser, AzureEnvironment azureEnvironment, Cance llationTokenSource cancellationTokenSource, Boolean forceAuthentication) at PnP.PowerShell.Commands.Base.ConnectOnline.ConnectInteractive() at PnP.PowerShell.Commands.Base.ConnectOnline.Connect(CancellationToken& cancellationToken) at PnP.PowerShell.Commands.Base.ConnectOnline.ProcessRecord() at System.Management.Automation.CommandProcessor.ProcessRecord() ScriptLineNumber : 1 ``` ### Steps to reproduce behavior ` connect-pnponline -url https://organization.sharepoint.com -Interactive` or ``` powershell $conn = Connect-PnPOnline ` -Thumbprint $CertificateThumbprint ` -Tenant organization.onmicrosoft.com ` -ClientId $clientId ` -Url https://organization.sharepoint.com/sites/somesite ` -ReturnConnection ``` ### What is the version of the Cmdlet module you are running? 1.3.0 From PSVersionTable: ``` Name Value ---- ----- PSVersion 5.1.14409.1005 PSEdition Desktop PSCompatibleVersions {1.0, 2.0, 3.0, 4.0...} BuildVersion 10.0.14409.1005 CLRVersion 4.0.30319.18444 WSManStackVersion 3.0 PSRemotingProtocolVersion 2.3 SerializationVersion 1.1.0.1 ``` Upon checking assembly version (from [this comment](https://github.com/pnp/powershell/issues/196) by @erwinvanhunen ): ``` powershell PS C:\Users\isv.sdahl> [AppDomain]::CurrentDomain.GetAssemblies() | ?{$_.Location -like "*Microsoft.SharePoint.Client.dl l"} | %{Get-Item $_.Location | select -ExpandProperty VersionInfo} ProductVersion FileVersion FileName -------------- ----------- -------- 16.1.20912.12000 16.1.20912.12000 C:\Program Files\WindowsPowerShell\Modules\PnP.PowerShell\1.3.0\Framework\Microsof... ``` .NET Version 4.5.2. ### Which operating system/environment are you running PnP PowerShell on? Shared marketplace for all users The current application only displays sale items for one account at a time. This allows users to purchase items from other users, but it is impossible to find items that are for sale without knowing an existing user's address. The application should have a tab that shows a list of _all_ items that are listed for sale.

In cluster mode, local IP is cached ### Questions In cluster mode, if domain name proxy is used, local IP is cached. If IP changes, the cluster cannot be accessed ### Version 4.0.0 ### Context > When creating a slot, actively pull the node information of the cluster, and cache the IP information and slot of the server response. However, if the IP under the domain name changes, it will not be able to access the cluster normally > The use of domain name access is mainly to shield the IP address of the intranet and avoid exposing the IP address of the intranet > Can I cache the original address? No way to hide referenced title in addition to author If I don't mention the author specifically in the text, I'll cite them like this: ``` Some critics argue that foo is bar [@brown1999 23]. Output: Some critics argue that foo is bar (Brown 23). ``` If I mention the author's name, I can add a - to the citation: ``` Some critics, like Brown, argue that foo is bar [-@brown1999 23]. Output: Some critics, like Brown, argue that foo is bar (23). ``` Great. But what if the author has more than one publication? Since I use the MLA CSL, this CSL will include the title of the work in order to disambiguate: ``` Some critics argue that foo is bar [@brown1999 23]. Output: Some critics argue that foo is bar (Brown, "The Fooiness of Bar," 23). Some critics, like Brown, in "The Fooiness of Bar," argue that foo is bar [-@brown1999 23]. Output: Some critics, like Brown, in "The Fooiness of Bar," argue that foo is bar ("The Fooiness of Bar," 23). ``` In the last example, the title of the work is repeated unnecessarily. Is there a way to remove both the author's name _and_ the title of the work, leaving only the page number? Something like this: ``` Some critics, like Brown, in "The Fooiness of Bar," argue that foo is bar [--@brown1999 23]. Output: Some critics, like Brown, in "The Fooiness of Bar," argue that foo is bar (23). ```

Render delay when using TreeView on-demand load **Describe the bug** Before #1406 had been implemented, I created a custom solution to handle on demand load when expanding the tree node. It worked very well for me and now with the release of 5.0.9 that has the support for it built-in, I thought I would try to switch out for that. However, upon trying the new behavior, I cannot understand why there is a delay for rendering the on-demand load data. Based on the documentation, there is a Task.Delay for 500ms but if you take that one out, it still takes time to render the children tree. I attached a snippet from TryMudBlazor to demonstrate the issue and the comparison with my custom solution as well. If you look at it, my solution renders much faster than the new on-demand load. Even if I try adding a delay to show the loading button animation, my solution would be still faster. **Expected behavior** Tree item children nodes should be rendered without substantial delay. **TryMudBlazor** https://try.mudblazor.com/snippet/caclufvLrtIdbyjg. Expand the node "Categories".

error during benchmark prevents start of mining when benchmark is complete It has cost me a lot of money over the years when I install a new card and let it benchmark overnight or whatever, making sure to check the box to start mining when benchmarking is complete. It pretty much never starts because any time a benchmark fails, it just sits there asking if it should retry the failed benchmarks. Please either have this dialog bypass after a timeout or just skip it entirely when the box to start mining was checked.

Slack Notification Integration **Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.** No, request is related to a requirement of a new shared plugin that can be used to configure CI build status broadcast towards one or multiple slack channels. **A clear and concise description of what the problem is. Ex. I'm always frustrated when [...]** I am always frustrated when I require to configure Slack plugins for each separate multi-pipeline build using individual Jenkins config file for each build project to send slack messages using closures (existing functionality) **A clear and concise description of what you want to happen.** I would like to be able to use a centralised plugin configuration that can be applied to multiple build projects, and can still be able to configure the default behaviour of the plugin using custom settings/parameters. **Describe alternatives you've considered** Use closures to inject specific code to send notification, which would require repeating the same code over and over again in multiple projects. **Additional context** Add any other context or screenshots about the feature request here.

Date parsing fails in latest JDK16 Currently we disabled JDK16 because it fails at date parsing [here](https://github.com/graphhopper/graphhopper/commit/598ecb0ff519a86112686e8a97adbfe9c3148aa7). Now it seems that the latest JDK16 integrated ["CLDR 38"](https://unicode-org.github.io/cldr-staging/charts/38/delta/en.html#Months%20-%20abbreviated%20-%20Standalone) and so the abbreviations for months changed from `Sep` to `Sept` and so the currently working code fails with the latest JDK16: ``` new SimpleDateFormat("yyyy MMM dd", Locale.UK).parse("2015 Sep 30"); ``` And indeed, [according to the docs](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/text/SimpleDateFormat.html#text), the 3 characters just mean that the month is abbreviated - not that exactly 3 characters are used: > Text: For formatting, if the number of pattern letters is 4 or more, the full form is used; otherwise a short or abbreviated form is used if available. For parsing, both forms are accepted, independent of the number of pattern letters. This is a bit ugly as we cannot change the OSM tagging. It seems to work with Locale.US or Locale.ROOT. See: https://bugs.openjdk.java.net/browse/JDK-8256837 **Update:** > I'd suggest specifying Locale.US in the formatter. Still, there is a very slim chance that CLDR could change the abbreviated name to "Sept" in Locale.US though

[BUG/ISSUE] dry run for data download w/ 13.0.1 not recognizing files are missing past day 2 of month for MERRA-2 global and GEOS-FP nested NA ### Description of the problem I cloned the GEOS-Chem code for version 13.0.1. I created two different run directories, one for GEOS-FP 0.25x0.3125 North America, one for MERRA-2 global 4x5, following the wiki; compiled the code; and did a dry run. for GEOS-FP 0.25x0.3125 NA it was for the month of July 2019. For MERRA-2 global 4x5 it was January - April 2018. I just noticed that in both cases, the only meteorological data that was recognized as required and missing files stopped on the 2nd day of the month. There are no files past day 2 of the initial month in the log files for the dry run, and so when I did the download data scripts based on those dry runs, no files past day 2 were downloaded of course. I tried to see if anyone had a similar issue but I haven't found. GEOS-FP files listed in the dry run log file, and downloaded for July 2019: `GEOSFP.20190701.A1.025x03125.nc GEOSFP.20190701.A3cld.025x03125.nc GEOSFP.20190701.A3dyn.025x03125.nc GEOSFP.20190701.A3mstC.025x03125.nc GEOSFP.20190701.A3mstE.025x03125.nc GEOSFP.20190701.I3.025x03125.nc GEOSFP.20190702.I3.025x03125.nc` Same but for MERRA-2 for January - April 2018, only has one folder for January 2018 with these files: `MERRA2.20180101.A1.4x5.nc4 MERRA2.20180101.A3cld.4x5.nc4 MERRA2.20180101.A3dyn.4x5.nc4 MERRA2.20180101.A3mstC.4x5.nc4 MERRA2.20180101.A3mstE.4x5.nc4 MERRA2.20180101.I3.4x5.nc4 MERRA2.20180102.I3.4x5.nc4` I followed the exact same workflow as what I had done with 13.0.0-rc, which successfully recognized all the files that were needed so for those dry runs of different time periods and meteorological fields I have been able to download multiple full months with all of the days of meteorological data. After switching to 13.0.1 they both seem to stop in day 2 after the I3 file. ### GEOS-Chem version 13.0.1 ### Description of modifications none ### Log files - Build log (if applicable): - Run logs (if applicable): dry run log for MERRA-2, 2018 Jan-Apr: [log.dryrun.201801_201804.txt](https://github.com/geoschem/geos-chem/files/6281330/log.dryrun.201801_201804.txt) with this input file: [input.geos.201801_201804.txt](https://github.com/geoschem/geos-chem/files/6281324/input.geos.201801_201804.txt) ; list of unique files log file: [log.dryrun.201801_201804.unique.txt](https://github.com/geoschem/geos-chem/files/6281372/log.dryrun.201801_201804.unique.txt) - dry run log for GEOS-FP, July 2019: [log.nested.dryrun.07.txt](https://github.com/geoschem/geos-chem/files/6281332/log.nested.dryrun.07.txt) with this input file [input.geos.txt](https://github.com/geoschem/geos-chem/files/6281333/input.geos.txt) ; list of unique files log file: [log.nested.dryrun.07.unique.txt](https://github.com/geoschem/geos-chem/files/6281355/log.nested.dryrun.07.unique.txt) - Run script (if applicable): run script for MERRA-2, 2018 Jan-Apr dry run: [dryrun_201801_201804.sbatch.txt](https://github.com/geoschem/geos-chem/files/6281375/dryrun_201801_201804.sbatch.txt) ; run script for downloading data: [dl_data_201801_201804.sbatch.txt](https://github.com/geoschem/geos-chem/files/6281380/dl_data_201801_201804.sbatch.txt) - run script for GEOS-FP, July 2019 dry run: [nested_dryrun_07.sbatch.txt](https://github.com/geoschem/geos-chem/files/6281335/nested_dryrun_07.sbatch.txt) ; run script for downloading data: [download_data_07.sbatch.txt](https://github.com/geoschem/geos-chem/files/6281346/download_data_07.sbatch.txt) ### Software versions - CMake version: 3.19.2 - Compilers (Intel or GNU, and version): gcc 9.3.0 - NetCDF version: 4.7.4 (C); 4.5.3 (Fortran)

allow endpoint mapping by http method currently an endpoint specific mapping applies to all http methods. This limits the usefulness of the endpoint mapping because you don't always need/want the mapping for all http methods. this applies the mappings to all methods (current behaviour): ``` openapi-processor-mapping: v2 map: paths: /foo: types: - type: from => to ``` this applies the mappings only to the given http method (new/additional behaviour): ``` openapi-processor-mapping: v2 map: paths: /foo: get: types: - type: A => B patch: types: - type: A => C ```

Bug: small window that displays info about the different slices of a pie chart appears when it shouldn't **Describe the bug** If a pie chart is a child of a tab container and its tab is not open, the small window that shows info about the different slices of the pie chart still appears. **To Reproduce** Steps to reproduce the behavior: 1. Create a node2D in a 2D scene. 2. Click on add child node and select tab container. 3. Click on add child node and create at least two tabs. 4. Return value of CompiledScript Hi, I was wondering how I can get the return value of the evaluation of a `CompiledScript` class. I noticed that it uses `GlobalMethodGenerator`, which supports a return value, but is internal, and its return value seems to just be discarded in the `CompiledScript.Execute(ScriptEngine engine)` method. I was wondering if you could update the library to include variants of `Evaluate` in `CompiledScript` like in the `ScriptEngine` class since it seems like it would require no internal changes and seems like a logical extension to me. The reason I want this is because I'm going to likely be evaluating the same script a lot of times in the same engine with possibly different global states, and want the return value, so rather than just calling `ScriptEngine.Evaluate(string)` every time, I'd like to cache the compilation. Thank you!

Change naming of output and error files of HPC jobs **Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.** Croupier/Cloudify atuomatically assigns a random ID to each job after a given job has started being executed through the run_jobs workflow. This is visible under the "Deployment Outputs/Capabilities" tab when you click on a Deployment. This ID is made up by the string "atos" followed by a combination of 6 random letters and numbers. ![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/29339953/118107736-6d6ef800-b3df-11eb-93c8-691b6725a55a.png) This become problematic when you want to inspect the .err and .out files associated with each job of the workflow. As we know, the install workflow creates a directory for a given workflow inside the target HPC cluster. When the run_job workflow is started, that directory is populated with a .script file for each job. ``` #!/bin/bash -l #SBATCH -N 1 #SBATCH -n 1 #SBATCH --ntasks-per-node=1 #SBATCH -t 00:40:00 #SBATCH -p thinnodes #SBATCH -e atos57xwq9.err #SBATCH -o atos57xwq9.out # DYNAMIC VARIABLES cd $CURRENT_WORKDIR bash <(sed -n '10,$p' $STORE/a3_climate_model_workflow/SEASONAL_SCRIPTS/CFS_SCRIPTS/download_CFSR.in) 00 ``` As each job is executed using the respective .script file created by Croupier inside the HPC system, the information generated during the execution of a given job is logged into two files, a .err and .out file (see SBATCH -e and -o flags inside .script file).These files are automatically named based on the ID that was assigned to them by Croupier as I explained above. If your workflow contains several jobs, then inspecting the log files become quite painful, because it's not clear from the name of the .err and .out files to what job inside the blueprint they belong to. ![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/29339953/118106698-2b918200-b3de-11eb-83c4-f4d64e474ec0.png) **Describe the solution you'd like** The solution is that Croupier assigns a sensible name to the .err and .out file. This could be the name of the individual job as written inside the blueprint. For example, if the job inside the blueprint is named "job_1", then the .err and .out files created inside HPC should be job_1.err and job_1.out.

Calling digitalWrite() in constructor on certain pins breaks timekleeping with TCD0 as millis source... Quote from: druckis3000 Tue Mar 02 2021 08:25:54 GMT-0500 (Eastern Standard Time) Exactly, there's nothing in there that should do that. I have already changed my project source code, but since I want to help, I wrote that code again in new sketch: ``` #include <mcp2515.h> #define LED_PIN 4 MCP2515 mcp(11); void setup() { Serial.begin(115200); pinMode(LED_PIN, OUTPUT); digitalWrite(LED_PIN, LOW); Serial.println("Ready!"); delay(1000); digitalWrite(LED_PIN, HIGH); delay(1000); digitalWrite(LED_PIN, LOW); delay(1000); } void loop() { } ``` With code above, led blinks almost instantaneously, and with code below, led blinks like it should: ``` #include <mcp2515.h> #define LED_PIN 4 MCP2515 *mcp; void setup() { mcp = new MCP2515(11); Serial.begin(115200); pinMode(LED_PIN, OUTPUT); digitalWrite(LED_PIN, LOW); Serial.println("Ready!"); delay(1000); digitalWrite(LED_PIN, HIGH); delay(1000); digitalWrite(LED_PIN, LOW); delay(1000); } void loop() { } ``` I was able to reproduce problem with CS pin disconnected, so I think you can reproduce same problem without even connected MCP2515 to MCU. I attached picture of my parameters used for uploading to ATtiny. I think it has something to do with constructor calling of globally defined variables, because it doesn't call different constructor for MCP2515 class no matter if it's defined in global scope, or just declared as a pointer and initialized inside a function with "new" operator. The thing is that MCP2515 has only one constructor. Maybe there are some things done before calling global var constructors or after calling them that has something to do with this problem? Edit: not related to MCP2515 library. This code can reproduce same problem: ``` #include <mcp2515.h> #define LED_PIN 4 class Test { public: Test(int a); private: int x; }; Test mcp(10); void setup() { Serial.begin(115200); pinMode(LED_PIN, OUTPUT); digitalWrite(LED_PIN, LOW); Serial.println("Ready!"); delay(1000); digitalWrite(LED_PIN, HIGH); delay(1000); digitalWrite(LED_PIN, LOW); delay(1000); } void loop(){} Test::Test(int a) { pinMode(a, OUTPUT); digitalWrite(a, HIGH); } ``` Problem disappears when commenting out digitalWrite(a, HIGH); line. Checked this problem with all pins and it happens only with 10 and 11 pin. Tried changing clock frequency, but it doesn't help. Also tried to take brand new ATtiny3216 IC, still same problem. Edit: The problem lies inside turnOffPWM(); function which is called at the end of digitalWrite() funtion. It's something to do with these lines of code:``` ``` // rigmarole that produces a glitch in the PWM uint8_t oldSREG=SREG; cli(); uint8_t TCD0_prescaler=TCD0.CTRLA&(~TCD_ENABLE_bm); TCD0.CTRLA = TCD0_prescaler; //stop the timer while (!(TCD0.STATUS & TCD_ENRDY_bm)); // wait until it's actually stopped _PROTECTED_WRITE(TCD0.FAULTCTRL, TCD0.FAULTCTRL & (~(1 << (bit_pos==0?6:7)))); TCD0.CTRLA = (TCD0_prescaler | TCD_ENABLE_bm); //re-enable it If I comment out last line, program works fine, no more problem with delay() function. ```

Unique Product IDs in Product groups Currently, it is allowed to have the same `product_id` twice in the list of `product_ids` in one product group element. See example below: ``` "product_groups": [ { "group_id": "CSAFGID-0001", "product_ids": [ "CSAFPID-0001", "CSAFPID-0001" ] } ``` However, this violates the rule [CSAF-5.1.4.1.2-1](https://docs.oasis-open.org/csaf/csaf-cvrf/v1.2/cs01/csaf-cvrf-v1.2-cs01.html#_Toc493508910). Therefore, I suggest to add an `"uniqueItems": true`.

dense optical flow in skip_empty mode sometimes throws unbound local error on prev_rgb Like this: ``` --------------------------------------------------------------------------- UnboundLocalError Traceback (most recent call last) <ipython-input-49-11df30484d0b> in <module> ----> 1 mg.flow.dense(skip_empty=True).show() c:\program files\python38\lib\site-packages\musicalgestures\_flow.py in dense(self, filename, pyr_scale, levels, winsize, iterations, poly_n, poly_sigma, flags, skip_empty) 109 out.write(rgb.astype(np.uint8)) 110 else: --> 111 out.write(prev_rgb.astype(np.uint8)) 112 else: 113 out.write(rgb.astype(np.uint8)) UnboundLocalError: local variable 'prev_rgb' referenced before assignment ``` This is probably an edge case when the first 2 processed frames are empty, and on the 2nd we try to recall the previous frame - which we never saved since that was empty as well. So we must feed back the first frame to prev_rgb in any case.

[API] Type Validator Should Handle Dictionaries **Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.** Currently, there is no way to define a validation rule such that the user can create their own object. This means that for things like "otherBenefits", anything that the user enters in there will be flagged by the validator as an unexpected field. **Describe the solution you'd like** There should be another advanced validation rule type for dictionary that should accept an object with any set of keys, but validates that the values are within an expected range. **Describe alternatives you've considered** It might also be possible to implement this out of the existing `object` type checking rule by adding a wildcard match. In this case, the user could still use the required fields checker for some fields in the object, but then just not throw unexpected attribute errors for anything the user doesn't define. While this seems to offer more flexibility for the user, it also doesn't match very well with the existing TypeScript type checker, and could increase code complexity.

.notdef ## Dev Effort 1D ## Description veraPDF 1.7.99 reports that this document: [notdef-T3.pdf](https://github.com/veraPDF/veraPDF-library/files/1194013/notdef-T3.pdf) violates 6.2.11.8 of ISO 19005-2:2011 (so do 3-Heights and callas). However, ".notdef" does not have a special meaning for Type 3 fonts. If you think that just naming a glyph ".notdef" makes it the .notdef glyph, then why is this document reported as valid? [notdef-T1c.pdf](https://github.com/veraPDF/veraPDF-library/files/1194027/notdef-T1c.pdf) Both documents use Differences to map a character code to a glyph named ".notdef".

The HttpSessionActivationListener interface is not used correctly HttpSessionActivationListener can be implemented by a class to get notified when its instance will be migrated to another VM. It cannot be registered as a listener in the ServletContext.

Support for multi-line factility notes ### User Story As a outreach coordinator I'd like to record status updates and short notes So that I can ensure that other coordinators have the most accurate up-to-date picture on facility needs/status ### Acceptance Criteria - [ ] The Notes field on the facility edit page ("/facility/edit/<id>") should allow multi line text text entry, similar to the multiline text entry permitted for some of the check in responses. - [ ] Pre-existing multi-line text values should be displayed with the line feeds as originally entered. - [ ] The Notes field should be sized to display 5 lines of text and be scrollable when more text exists (for both edit page and facility view page) ### Notes This issue assumes that the existing API functionality and JSON payloads can handle multiline notes as-is. If this is NOT true, please create an issue in Bmore-Responsive to add multi-0line support on back end.

Needs a suitable citation feature similar to GNU parallels Even if the CITATION text isn't completely finished because we don't have URLs, publish dates etc from a preprint or an article, it is important to have the essential process for showing the citation information and silencing it if needed. The milestone suitable for academic use means that the methodologies have all been documented in a preprint, it does not mean that the methods are necessarily sound. No warranties are made about how you use this software. There is no guarantee that my formula for the Markov probabilities is correct, there is no guarantee that a first order Markov model is a suitable null model, there is no guarantee that a uniform random distribution is suitable for the frequency (`p(x)`) of the 0th k-mer in the null model. The counts are accurate and the methods applied are honest, but I can't talk about when an dhow this should be used until I better understand my audience and my peers who will review this work.

Change the way of integrating RBAC API and Management API to a one Enforcer I think the best way to integrate IEnforcer (rbac api) and ManagementEnforcer (management api) to a one IEnforcer is use `Extension Method` to implement it. Here are some reasons: 1. IEnforcer can be a simple and clean interface. 2. We can maintain the RBAC and Management API at different class, and we can easy to add new helper type API. 4. Follow the CARP desgin. It will become a break change, we should change the protect field to Read-only property (also GetModel method can do it) and delete the `InternalEnforcer`, `ManagementEnforcer` and `CoreEnforcer` and convert them to a Enforcer class which only includes the API in `InternalEnforcer` and `CoreEnforcer` in now version). **Relate comment:** https://github.com/casbin/Casbin.NET/pull/55#issuecomment-662766747

NTP doesn't work anymore in v2: DNSSEC validation failed ## Description Time update with NTP doesn't work anymore in the new v2 image with Buildroot 2021.02. The log is full of errors: ``` Feb 02 16:38:48 yioremote systemd-resolved[142]: [ü°ï] DNSSEC validation failed for question . IN DNSKEY: signature-expired Feb 02 16:38:48 yioremote systemd-resolved[142]: [ü°ï] DNSSEC validation failed for question com IN DS: signature-expired Feb 02 16:38:48 yioremote systemd-resolved[142]: [ü°ï] DNSSEC validation failed for question com IN DNSKEY: signature-expired Feb 02 16:38:48 yioremote systemd-resolved[142]: [ü°ï] DNSSEC validation failed for question google.com IN DS: signature-expired Feb 02 16:38:48 yioremote systemd-resolved[142]: [ü°ï] DNSSEC validation failed for question google.com IN SOA: signature-expired Feb 02 16:38:48 yioremote systemd-resolved[142]: [ü°ï] DNSSEC validation failed for question time4.google.com IN DS: signature-expired Feb 02 16:38:48 yioremote systemd-resolved[142]: [ü°ï] DNSSEC validation failed for question time4.google.com IN SOA: signature-expired Feb 02 16:38:48 yioremote systemd-resolved[142]: [ü°ï] DNSSEC validation failed for question time4.google.com IN AAAA: signature-expired Feb 02 16:38:48 yioremote systemd-resolved[142]: [ü°ï] DNSSEC validation failed for question time4.google.com IN A: signature-expired ``` ## How to Reproduce Steps to reproduce the behavior: 1. Use v2.0.0-rc1 image 2. Run initial configuration 3. See time in UI: doesn't get updates 4. See errors with `journalctl -f` ## Expected behavior Time is updated with ntp ## Your Environment * Version used: v2.0.0-rc1 * Running on: - YIO Remote ## Additional context Similar issue: https://bbs.archlinux.org/viewtopic.php?id=240427 systemd now uses DNSSEC by default with downgrade if the servers don't support it. Default time servers are from Google. They support DNSSEC. Initial boot has a date of Feb 2 which makes DNS requests invalid, because of the timeframe. So the ntp servers cannot be resolved and the time never gets synchronized... Possible solutions: - Manually set initial time. Bad user experience if the remote is switched off for a while and the time has to be manually set again. - Use standalone ntp client and disable systemd ntp. This might still not work if the server name cannot be resolved. - Disable DNSSEC in systemd.

Clean files created by Browser library at start of the test execution When there are multiple test executions, the files created by Browser library are not cleaned by the library. This will leak files to the file system and consume space. Instead when test execution is started, we should remove the screenshots and videos created be the library. User can delete files in an external script or configure their CI system to clean the whole workspace, but the Browser library should be able to clean files it created from the previous runs. When test execution starts, we should check is there existing files created by the Browser library. If there are those files should be delated. This should be done only one time, multiple imports or using the `Import Library` keyword should not cause cleaning do in multiple times. Also the cleaning should happen before the Browser library has created new files in the file system. The #476 is related and should be done first, to ease the cleaning.

StratCon - Scenario location and date moves each day so can never fight battle 23:44:38,882 INFO [mekhq.MekHQ] {AWT-EventQueue-0} showInfo(), line 364 : MekHQ 0.49.0-SNAPSHOT Compiled on 2021-04-20T23:51:02Z Today is 2021-04-22 Java vendor AdoptOpenJDK Java version 11.0.10 Platform Windows 10 10.0 (amd64) Total memory available to MegaMek: 1,048,576 kB ### Description Landed at contract planet. Day I landed also happened to be Monday and start of first contract week. So day I landed it generated a Pursuit scenario to happen in 1 day. Went to map pane to deploy lance to that scenario and did so. Advanced day. Now scenario date had moved forward 1 day and "enemy force" icon on map had moved south one hex. Advance day again. Same thing. Scenario date moved forward 1 day and enemy force moved south one hex. Etc. Each time this happened it showed I lost a VP point on map page. The moving on map part is odd but the day advancing keeps you from ever starting the battle. I reloaded a number of times and tried to deploy force only on day of battle and other various things, but could never get it to work. Also I could deploy an new lance to it each day and my deployed lance would move with the enemy force icon. So after 3 days enemy force had moved south 3 hexes and had 3 of my lances assigned to it. In the screen attached enemy force started in hex 8.1 and moved south one hex each day. The only oddity I can think of on my end is that I normally assign lances fight/defend/scout on first day I land and since this happened to be on a Monday the day I landed I did not have all 4 lances required by contract deployed on briefing tab. Eventually just reloaded to day before I landed, set my deployments before I landed and got a new scenario the first week. Saves and screens attached. Customize client generators ## Generators customization I want to change the behavior of generator. For example, add some JSDoc generation. It will be huge and quite easy boost for whole library, if we do next way. ### 1 Create custom client object ```ts [OutputClient.REACT_QUERY]: { client: myCustomGeneratorHere, // <---- HERE msw: generateMSW, header: generateReactQueryHeader, dependencies: getReactQueryDependencies, footer: generateReactQueryFooter, title: generateReactQueryTitle, }, //... ``` ### 2 Include that in project Could be done in 2 ways #### 2A tell program, that we want to use `customClientGeneratorFunc` here: https://github.com/anymaniax/orval/blob/master/src/core/generators/client.ts#L177 ```ts const generator = GENERATOR_CLIENT[outputClient]; const client = generator.client(verbOption, options); ``` Custom client could be passed - as `override.client` property - as `output.client` as function: ```js const generator = typeof outputClient === 'function' ? outputClient : GENERATOR_CLIENT[outputClient]; // this should be done in all spots where GENERATOR_CLIENT is invoked. ``` #### 2B Make `GENERATOR_CLIENT` a singleton, which could be mutated. ```js // generators/client.ts const GENERATOR_CLIENT = {...}; export function addGeneratorClient(key, obj) { GENERATOR_CLIENT[key] = obj; } // in orval.config.js import { addGeneratorClient } from 'orval'; addGeneratorClient('custom-query', { client : foo(){}, // ... }); export default { output: { client: 'custom-query' } } ``` Of course that could be realized with class and private properties, anyway - idea was modifying global object with own generators. ## steps are 1. make this tiny code change 2. adopt change typings for new changes 3. update documentation --- ## Profit Users can change main functions with their own just in few operations. It would be easy to change just one generator (i. e. `client`) and the rest ones (`msw`, `title`) could be imported as is.

Edge de-select event report to many de-selected edges at specific case... Hi, Thanks for a fantastic work with Vis. I've started to integrate it to my Blazor solution, and so far it's really good stuff. There is one corner case I've noticed with Vis, and that is the reporting on de-selected edges. Mostly it runs as espected, but there is one case that gives the issue. If you create a hierarchy with Vis, e.g a simple one with five nodes and four edges, where one node has more than one edge. In my case the middle node has three edges (root and two children nodes). If I select the middle node, then I get good reporting of one node and three edges selected. If I select any edge not already selected, then I get the good report of three de-selected edges and one new selected edge. But if I select one of the edges already selected (by the middle node selection), then I get a report of three edges de-selected but not the selected edge as selected. This means that my solution now thinks that no edge is selected, but Vis is displaying the clicked edge as selected. Another issue is with update and delete operations. The same, if I select the middle node, the node and the three edges are selected (this is fine). If I delete the node, then the node and edges are deleted (this is fine too), but there is no report of the edges (or the node) being de-selected. Since the edges and the node are now gone, it would be logical if the same items also were reported as de-selected. This is a minor issue, since I do get report of the items being removed (so I can de-select them myself accordingly). The select issue (above) is somewhat worse, since it derails my solution (not synchronized) with Vis depending on how I select the edges in the graph (selecting nodes however works fine with edges and nodes reported correctly reported). Thanks

Bug: colon issue in query binding **Describe the bug** Query binding fails when using date_format with hours in it (colon issue) If there is a colon in the query, the query builder thinks it is a named bind, and handles the query in that way, even if you have ? bindings. **CodeIgniter 4 version** v4.1.1 **Affected module(s)** system/Database/Query.php Line 352 **Expected behavior, and steps to reproduce if appropriate** Old version: `$hasNamedBinds = strpos($sql, ':') !== false && strpos($sql, ':=') === false;` This returns true when query has `date_format(now(), '%d-%m-%Y %H:%i')`, but in the query I only use ? as binding, so it won't find any :mybind: binding. suggestion: `$hasNamedBinds = preg_match('/:[a-z._-]+:/',$sql);` With this fix, all my queries are working. **Context** - OS: debian 10 - Web server: Apache 2.4.38 - PHP version: 7.3.27

false color model instrumentation plugins #### Rajawali Version or Branch master #### Summary Sometimes, when troubleshooting a scene, it is helpful to instrument the model view, we could use a couple of material plugins to render false color surfaces of model positions and normals. #### Steps to Reproduce ``` static class FalseColorRenderer extends Renderer { public FalseColorRenderer(Context context) { super(context); } @Override protected void initScene() { try { getCurrentScene().setBackgroundColor(Color.BLUE & Color.GRAY); DirectionalLight key = new DirectionalLight(-3, 4, 5); key.setPower(5.0f); getCurrentScene().addLight(key); Material material = new Material(); material.setColor(Color.CYAN & Color.GRAY); material.addPlugin(new PositionColorMaterialPlugin()); //material.addPlugin(new NormalColorMaterialPlugin()); material.setDiffuseMethod(new DiffuseMethod.Lambert()); material.setAmbientColor(Color.DKGRAY); material.enableLighting(true); material.enableTime(true); Object3D obj = new Cube(2); obj.setMaterial(material); getCurrentScene().addChild(obj); Animation3D anim = new RotateOnAxisAnimation(Vector3.Axis.Z, 360); anim.setTransformable3D(obj); anim.setDurationDelta(6); anim.setRepeatMode(Animation.RepeatMode.INFINITE); getCurrentScene().registerAnimation(anim); anim.play(); getCurrentCamera().setUpAxis(Vector3.Axis.Z); getCurrentCamera().setPosition(5, -4, 3); getCurrentCamera().setLookAt(obj.getPosition()); } catch (Exception e) { Log.e(getClass().getSimpleName(), e.getMessage()); } } @Override public void onOffsetsChanged(float v, float v1, float v2, float v3, int i, int i1) { } @Override public void onTouchEvent(MotionEvent motionEvent) { } } ``` #### Screenshot ![2020-12-30](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/17471201/103403867-8b118400-4b06-11eb-808c-581da0887cde.png)

The solution will be to handle this keys and allow then to work as expected: - **up/down Arrorws:** Should move between previously typed commands - **left/right Arrows:** Should allow to move in the current input and edit it as needed - Other Keys: Should not mess the input and work as expected on any cli

Allow @Description and @ModuleDescription in Excel Workbook and Worksheet modules **Justification** Most of the VBA I code is in locked down Excel Workbook projects designed to take user input and external data and output summary information, reports or files for import into another program. In this use, individual Excel Worksheets play unique rolls in the process that need to be documented. **Description** I would love to extend Rubberduck's indispensable `@ModuleDescription` and `@Description` annotations to include Workbook and Worksheet modules and event the overall Project (Excel or other MS Office file). Worksheets themselves are often intended for specific purposes, such as data entry, syncing data from external sources or summary reporting and a back-end description and I think that documenting that along with the purpose of VBA in those Worksheets is just as helpful here as it is in code and class modules. In addition to regular procedures, Worksheets can also have Event procedures that need to be documented (I currently document them using my pre-Rubberduck method as a comment inside the procedure). Here's an example description for a `Workbook_AfterSave()` event: > ' DESCRIPTION: Recalculates the -FileNameError- named Range which compares the period in the file name to the period on the Worksheet. Worksheets can have Form Controls that point to procedures on the sheet and ActiveX Controls with procedures directly linked to the procedure name such as `Private Sub MyActiveXButton_Click()`. `@ProjectDescription` annotations would also be useful ‚Äì entered in the Workbook module and displayed when the project is selected in the Code Explorer.

Signals with zero value fallback to initial value in frame encoding **Describe the bug** When encoding frames signals with value zero will fallback to the initial value instead of the value zero. **To Reproduce** ```python signal1 = LinSignal('Signal1', 8, 255) frame1 = LinFrame(1, 'Frame1', 1, {0: signal1}) encoded = frame1.raw({ "Signal1": 0 }) print(encoded) ``` The example above is going to print 255, which is the initial value instead of the expected 0. **Expected behavior** The signal should be encoded into the value zero in this case. **Additional context** The fault is in lin.py file, line number 77 where `dict.get` is used to check the existence of the key, it works as intended when the signal is missing from the dictionary but also evaluates to `False` when the signal value is zero. In the code coverage this branch is fully covered even though there are no test cases that would test the scenario where the signal is missing from the dictionary.

OpenClose for blinds: invert openPercentage? The OpenClose trait works a little bit strange for blinds. Example (tested in German): Set the blinds to 90% Actually the result is that the blinds are set to 90% open. So not the blinds are 90% visible, but the blinds are nearly completely open. From user perspective this sounds really strange, as you think that 100% means closed and not open for blinds. Of course, if you think about a door it's the other way around (100% = open, 0% = closed). I would suggest to include an invert attribute to the OpenClose SYNC response so that the result of "set the blinds to 90%" results in openPercentage = 10%.

Image pull policy should be "Always" [Link to action item](https://staging.insights.fairwinds.com/orgs/0512/clusters/0512/action-items?ReportType=polaris&ResourceNamespace=cert-manager&ResourceKind=Deployment&ResourceName=cert-manager-cainjector&ResourceContainer=cert-manager) **Description:** Relying on cached versions of a Docker image can become a security vulnerability. By default, an image will be pulled if it isn't already cached on the node attempting to run it. This can result in variations in images that are running per node, or potentially provide a way to gain access to an image without having direct access to the ImagePullSecret. With that in mind, it's often better to ensure the a pod has pullPolicy: Always specified, so images are always pulled directly from their source. **Remediation:** Set image pull policy to always, e.g. `imagePullPolicy: Always`

Wrong templated types in recursive templated function When calling recursively a templated function, types seems to be wrong. ### Steps to reproduce Compile the following code: ```ts function foo<T1,T2>(): string { if(isInteger<T2>()){ return foo<T2, T1>(); } return nameof<T1>(); } export function test(): string { return foo<f64, i32>(); } ``` ### Expected behavior Function `test()` should return `"i32"`. But this code generate an unexpected infinite loop because of recursive call with wrong types: ```WebAssembly (func $module/foo<i32,i32> (result i32) i32.const 1 drop call $module/foo<i32,i32> return ) (func $module/foo<f64,i32> (result i32) i32.const 1 drop call $module/foo<i32,i32> ;; Should be `call $module/foo<i32,f64>` return ) (func $module/test (result i32) call $module/foo<f64,i32> ) ```

The Interpolate setting of ValueGradientDriver<floatQ> doesn't work properly ## Description A rotation driven by the ValueGradientDriver<floatQ> (with the Interpolate field = True) snaps between rotation points rather than rotating between points continuously when the Progress field of the ValueGradientDriver changes. ## Relevant issues Plausibly related to https://github.com/Frooxius/NeosPublic/issues/1640 and https://github.com/Frooxius/NeosPublic/issues/1664 ## To Reproduce 1. Start empty world 2. Create a new object with dev tip (to visualise changes) 3. Add a ValueGradientDriver<floatQ> and drive the rotation of the object. 4. In the inspector window, press the Add button on the ValueGradientDriver component to add two set points to the component Points list. 5. Enter arbitrary values into the ValueGradientDriver set points (e.g. [0,0,0] and [30,0,0]) and drag the position slider of point 1 to 1.00. 6. Ensure the Interpolate field is True 7. Dragging the Progress slider of the ValueGradientDriver results in the rotation of the object snapping between the two set point values. ## Expected behavior Interpolation by the component is expected to provide continuous rotation values between set points, analogous to the Constant S/Lerp LogiX nodes. ## Bug information (please complete the following information): - How often does it happen: Always - Does the bug persist after restarting Neos? Adding architecture support for ARM Hi, Buildbot should support the most common popular architectures used in gentoo, these are amd64, arm and arm64. As a first step support for ARM architecture would be great: - Create a dedicated builder for ARM (kernel 4.x as a first step, then gentoo_sources and other_sources) - Cross build linux kernel for ARM (use an armv7a hardfloat toolchain) - Test with qemu-system-arm for the vexpress a9 target (vexpress or versatile are usually the most tested and ready to use targets for ARM on qemu )

Problem loading Filament on a MMU single mode print Hi, i had to upgrade my printers from 3.0.4 to 3.1.0 because of upgrading SUPERpinda. Now i got a strange behaviour when starting a single-color-print with a cold extruder. in 3.0.4 it was the way, that when you choose the filament slot, the filament will be loaded until the ir sensor is triggered and the MMU LED lights green. Then it waited for heating up the nozzle and then it was loaded into the nozzle. With 3.1.0 and no other changes, all of my machines are having trouble. The MMU tries to load to a cold nozzle, but when triggering the ir sensor, the MMU pushes on and on, through the extruder pulley straight into the cold nozzle. Then the MMU slot starts flashing red. And if you wait, nothing more happens. This can only be resolved by unloading the filament (right MMU button), waiting for heating up, entering the MMU setup mode and leaving this mode. Do you have a workaround for this?

`before_batch_transfer` and `after_batch_transfer` hooks in LightningDataModule ## üöÄ Feature Can we have two additional hooks in LightningDataModule? Something like `before_batch_transfer_to_device`, `after_batch_transfer_to_device`, although these can be renamed to something else. ### Motivation - `before_batch_transfer_to_device`: This can help apply transformations or augmentations to a batch before it is transferred to the device. - `after_batch_transfer_to_device`: This can help apply transformations or augmentations to a batch after it is transferred to the device. For eg we can perform data augmentation in the GPU for a batch using Kornia. ### Alternatives As of now, it can be done by overriding the `transfer_batch_to_device` hook but a separate hook makes more sense here I think. If approved I can send a PR :)

inconsistency between attribute shapeEnd and drawn 'E' in move mode attribut shapeEnd (and shapeStart) retrieval check for ``` myNBEdge->getGeometry().back().distanceSquaredTo2D(getParentJunctions().back()->getNBNode()->getPosition()) < 2 ``` whereas the rendering code checks ``` myNBEdge->getGeometry().back() != getParentJunctions().back()->getNBNode()->getPosition() ``` I think the tolerant check used by attribute retrieval is more useful

I can start an InitVM built with the wrong elbe Version elbe v2.2: waynix@my-elbe-vm:~$ elbe initvm start --directory=initvm_built_with_elbe_v2.1 ***** waynix@my-elbe-vm:~$ elbe initvm stop elbe v2.1 is used in initvm, this is not compatible with elbe v2.2 that is used on this machine. Please install same versions of elbe in initvm and on your machine.

Jammed at walking area with very low demand one pedestrain and one bike meet within a working area. After the bike made an emergency braking, both of the objects stay at their locations for around 60 sec and then the jammed warning appears. Another pedestrian is affected and also in a jammed state.

'oauthlib.oauth1.rfc5849.signature' has no attribute 'signature_base_string' in 3.0.2 <!-- Thank you for contributing. These HTML comments will not render in the issue, but you can delete them once you've read them if you prefer! --> ### Bug description <!-- Use this section to clearly and concisely describe the bug. --> Yesterday I had the same issue as #29 updating my hub. I looked for a while but now I understand the problem. `ltiauthenticator` requires `oauthlib>=3.0` but `signature_base_string` was introduced in `oauthlib=3.1.0` see : https://github.com/oauthlib/oauthlib/compare/v3.0.2...v3.1.0#diff-e4bece930efcad3722195569e685ec7360baee26226b7371efd64d2a8a46e947L141 I don't know how it was working until now

RFC | Handling custom CSS selectors in UIDL With the latest update we support the `pseudo` selectors using a `element-state` attribute in the `referencedStyles` in UIDL. We pre-defined a fixed set of states like ```js export type UIDLElementStyleStates = 'hover' | 'active' | 'focus' | 'disabled' ``` So, we technically cannot define a custom selector like which we hacked around previously using `nested-styles` ```js "&[data-is-expanded='true']": { "type": "nested-style", "content": { "height": "$props.expandableHeight" } } ``` We need to discuss a first class support for handling such scenarios in the UIDL using `referencedStyles`

Product/variant metafields consistently inaccessible through cache (incremental builds) This is a somewhat specific issue which may be difficult to reproduce but the long story short I'm seeing here is: - Using `5.0.0-rc.21` - Defining a product fragment pulling both product-level and variant-level metafields (below) - Running `gatsby clean` and then running the development server pulls in all the data I would expect (ie, matches Shopify) - Killing the development server and running it again results in missing metafield data (logging out the product data makes it clear that the metafield arrays are inexplicably empty) - Running `gatsby clean` and re-running the development server again pulls all the metafield data - This is also reflected with `gatsby build` and `gatsby serve`, requiring `gatsby clean` in between each `serve` to get the correct data - This behavior is also reflected in GraphiQL, filtering to show the same product both times - First build: ![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6181127/117589171-a06a7080-b0ed-11eb-89ee-19515c000478.png) - Second build: ![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6181127/117589065-0c98a480-b0ed-11eb-9fa8-88351501fddb.png) Product fragment used throughout my project: ``` fragment ProductFragment on ShopifyProduct { id shopifyId storefrontId handle description title tags productMetafields: metafields { productId internal { type } value namespace key } priceRangeV2 { minVariantPrice { amount } maxVariantPrice { amount } } options { name values } images { gatsbyImageData } variants { title id compareAtPrice availableForSale inventoryQuantity price shopifyId storefrontId selectedOptions { name value } product { images { gatsbyImageData } } variantMetafields: metafields { productVariantId key namespace value } } } ``` Is this somehow expected behavior or are there any obvious things I should be looking into to fix this? Currently it's resolvable by just always clearing the cache but that's a bit time-consuming and, to my knowledge, this never used to be necessary before adding the product-level metafield information (which I believe was recently merged in, here: https://github.com/gatsbyjs/gatsby-source-shopify/pull/134)

[FEATURE] A better way to access string value of ClassLabels ## üö®üö® Feature Request - [x] A new implementation (Improvement, Extension) ### Is your feature request related to a problem? Accessing the string value of ClassLabels is inconvenient and complicated as illustrated below:- ```python import numpy as np from hub import schema, Dataset my_schema = {"label": schema.ClassLabel(names=["red", "green", "blue"])} ds = Dataset("./data/classlabel_ds", shape=(5,), schema=my_schema) ds["label", 0] = 1 ds["label", 1] = 2 ds["label", 2] = 0 # this works well assert ds["label", 0].compute() == 1 assert (ds["label", 0:3].compute() == np.array([1, 2, 0])).all() # getting the actual string label is a little more complicated cl_label = my_schema["label"] assert cl_label.int2str(ds["label", 0].compute()) == "green" assert [cl_label.int2str(ds["label", i].compute()) for i in range(3)] == ["green", "blue", "red"] ``` ### If your feature will improve `HUB` Yes, it will make accessing the string value of ClassLabels much easier ### Description of the possible solution Add a parameter called get_label to .compute() of TensorView that is False by default. If it is set to True:- - if the dtype of TensorView is not ClassLabel, do nothing - if the dtype of TensorView is ClassLabel, use the dtype to convert the result into string(s) using int2str **Teachability, Documentation** ```python # ideal implementation, continued from the code above assert ds["label", 0].compute(get_label=True) == "green" assert ds["label", 0:3].compute(get_label=True) == ["green", "blue", "red"] ```

Decouple 'trusts/safemethods' from manifest? From https://github.com/neo-project/neo/issues/287#issuecomment-494075858 I get that > trusts is an array of contract that can call "me" without UI warnings display. and from the [NEP itself](https://github.com/neo-project/proposals/blob/3e492ad05d9de97abb6524fb9a73714e2cdc5461/nep-15.mediawiki#safemethods) > If a method is marked as safe, the user interface will not give any warnings when it is called by any other contract. This seems presentation logic, not manifest business logic. Why must it be hardcoded in the manifest? The manifest creator should not determine for a client what a client finds worthy to be notified about. Instead I think an event notification that a contract method is called by entity X is what is needed. A client can subscribe to such an event and let the user decide what methods it wants to listen to for what contracts. **Problem scenario** Take a contract with 2 methods `contract_update` and `say_hooray`. The manifest states `contract_update` is trusted because they might want to hide flaws or have actual malicious intentions and try to do a silent update. So now the client will not be notified when `contract_update` is called. This is the exact opposite of what I'd like as a client. As a client I'd like to select exactly `contract_update` as the method I want to be notified about and I don't care about `say_hooray` being called. @RavenXce you rightfully [pointed out](https://github.com/neo-project/neo/issues/287#issuecomment-423723363) that it currently would be hard for a client to detect who calls who. What's your thoughts on the above?

jitting a complex neural network While experimenting with a complex neural network as a jax machine, I came across compilation issues which impact the performance of optimizing. The neural network which I am using is pretty complex in terms of code (it contains a nested loop, which is generally hard for jax to compile), but the operations it does are pretty simple and should not take much time. Indeed, compiling this network in the first optimization step takes a long time. Doing the first optimization step indeed takes a lot of time due to the initial compilation of functions. Normally, you would expect that after this first iteration, execution time improves as jax can reuse the jitted functions from the first step. However, when profiling the code, I observed that at every iteration step, jax has to do an additional compilation, which takes up to 80% of the execution time of a single iteration in my case. As far as I can trace it, I think the problem lies in the fact that the array of connected matrix elements has a variable batch size, due to different matrix elements being zero with different samples. It is known that jax compilation needs a specific shape as input of a function to be jitted and reusing the compiled version for inputs with different shapes is not possible. Hence, every time an unknown shape is passed to a function to be jitted, jax has to recompile the function. The fact that the array of connected matrix elements has variable shape, essentially means that the forward pass to compute the log probabilities has to be recompiled every iteration, which becomes a bottleneck for complex architectures. I think a fix with minimal impact would be to divide the forward pass of a batch of samples in minibatches with a fixed shape, and padding the last minibatch with zeros. In this way, every time the forward function is called, its input has the same shape and jax can reuse the compiled function.

Keep the order of document when export How to reproduce the behaviour --------- I have been annotating a corpus of ~7.6k documents in sequence labeling mode. I then exported the data to do some analytics and found out that the order in which the data is exported does not correspond to the order in the annotation tool, even though the project never had the randomization option turned on. I updated Doccano to the lastest release (1.0.5) today and exported again, only to find that this second export had a different order from the first export. Checking some samples did not reveal a consistent pattern (offset +/- X, etc.). This seemed unfortunate, since this would break the ability to export data, process it and then go back to doccano and pull up specific datapoints for revision/curation. A sanity check of the ascending document IDs then showed that the order in the Docanno interface is based on the ascending "id" field, which fortunately is not a GUID. In the export, however, this ordering seems to not be maintained. After reordering the export according to the "id" field, the order matches that in the editor and allows for going and back and checking data points. While reordering after export is a functioning workaround, I presume this behavior is not intended and hence am filing it as a bug. Your Environment --------- <!-- Include details of your environment.--> * Operating System: Ubuntu 18.04 * Python Version Used: default as per docker config * When you install doccano: Early July 2020, update to latest release on July 23 * How did you install doccano: Local `docker-compose` deployment

Ability to extend routing table Right now we can map only [consumer group, topic] pair to specific consumer class and if, for example, topic contains different message types ‚Äî we're ought to implement custom router inside the consumer, which is not ideal because abstractions are broken. Would be awesome to replace ```ruby class MyTopicConsumer def consume message_type :ping do message_version 1 do PingProcessor::V1.process(params) end message_version 2 do PingProcessor::V2.process(params) end end end end ``` with ```ruby consumer_groups.draw do consumer_group 'my_group' do topic 'my_topic' do message_type :ping do message_version 1 do consumer PingConsumer::V1 end message_version 2 do consumer PingConsumer::V2 end end end end end ``` ## Describe the solution you'd like Right now it's ```ruby topic = Persistence::Topics.fetch(group_id, kafka_message.topic) consumer = Persistence::Consumers.fetch(topic, kafka_message.partition) ``` in `{Message,Batch}Delegator`, which is IMHO a bit confusing since we have `Karafka::Routing::Router` that is described as `Karafka framework Router for routing incoming messages to proper consumers`. Essentially it's multilevel hash with `routing_table[consumer_group_id][topic_name][partition] = Consumer.new`, would be good to merge `Karafka::Persistence` with `Karafka::Routing` and generalize it to some kind of middleware that just filters messages ```ruby Router.register_middleware(:topic, TopicMiddleware) class TopicMiddleware attr_accessor :consumer # filter is `my_topic` in case of `topic 'my_topic'` in routing table def initialize(filter) @filter = ->(kafka_message) { kafka_message.topic == filter } end def call(kafka_message) @filter.call(kafka_message) end end ``` and router that tries to find middleware chain that matches the message and gets consumer from it. It's a rough idea, but if it's more or less good idea and could be accepted ‚Äî I can try to make it more real-life. Unanswered questions: 1. How batch consuming should be handled 2. Should we provide a way to replace middlewares with monolithic router or performance reasons? 3. Should we get consumer from first successful middleware chain or more elaborate rules should be available? 4. ‚Ä¶ ## Describe alternatives you've considered Consumer as a router? Monkeypatching karafka?

[coverage] Use `no cover` instead of `no-cover` ## üöÄ Refactoring As far as I know from - the docs: https://coverage.readthedocs.io/en/latest/excluding.html - the number of search results on GitHub - `pragma: no cover` https://github.com/search?l=Python&q=pragma%3A+no+cover&type=code - `pragma: no-cover` https://github.com/search?l=Python&q=pragma%3A+no-cover&type=code , we should use `pragma: no cover` instead of `pragma: no-cover`. I guess there's no difference between them, but most of the projects employ `pragma: no cover` as in the docs. (This should not be a high priority, but for consistency, we can start to use `no cover`.)

[BUG]: PATH requires correction for GOROOT **Describe the bug** The `$PATH` is not correctly set to include the go executable. **Expected behavior** The `$PATH` var must include the bin subfolder of the `$GOROOT`, not `$GOROOT` itself.

Important questions for discussion Duplicating the unresolved questions & suggestions which need **discussion** (not plain old bugs) in a separate post, so it would be possible to read them through. Please share your thoughts on them, some are quite important: - [x] C3M0_A: killcount is totally off, it may be better to disable showing it at all. Pre-placed zombies count towards kills, spawned ones not, and it is impossible for a player to distinguish them. > https://github.com/Realm667/WolfenDoom/commit/3e1b331ddba3dce9f7759589d3d062b3ae0fc4b9. Thanks, @AFADoomer! --N00b, 21 Apr 2021 - [x] C3M0_A: absolutely nothing indicates that to start assaulting the SS HQ you have to gather all three weapons (Browning, G43, Nebelwerfer) from their specific spots. Else the player can only wonder what to do after grabbing two keys and, for example, missing the butcher's with the rifle. I think the corresponding primary objective should be re-added. > Well done, @Talon1024, thank you very much! --N00b, 22 Apr 2021 - [x] C3M0_A: Is it really necessary for the player to wait several minutes until the Nemesis wakes up again after destroying the SS HQ? Could you please force Nemesis to revive himself when the player leaves the area, or at least give another message the player to wait a bit 'until the reinforcements arrive'? > As far as I know the behaviour has been changed by @Talon1024 , maybe he can just confirm and check this issue --T667 (14th April) - [x] C3M0_A: I have severe lag in the city part of the level, I have to pause the game every few seconds to avoid stuttering. Could anyone please think of some measures to reduce the workload on the CPU, maybe adding more one-sided linedefs which block the view, or replacing lots of small decorations with bigger ones? > This really needs a map-side fix. Run the level with 'stat rendertimes' and check out the S: stat... Even with more aggressive culling (if I enable it for all models, lights, and other decor) this area renders a ton of sprites/actors at a time. There are *3500+* things in the city portion of the map, compared to just over 3000 in the mansion and start area, and not quite 1900 in the underground area. - AFA (21 Apr 2021) > @AFADoomer By 'more aggressive culling', what values do you mean? The area works generally quite okay for me now with Vulkan and 4096 on everything, the S: is around 2.0, but when exploring the map there are lots of lag spikes, S: temporarily becomes around 300 and more (is it measured in milliseconds?). I suspect it is because of new models having to be loaded from the HDD, and wonder if something like [PrecacheClasses](https://zdoom.org/wiki/MAPINFO/Map_definition#PrecacheClasses) could help with this. --N00b, 22 Apr 2021 > I set up my local build to also cull all model-based decorations and lights. Probably going to hide the capability behind a CVar and commit tonight. I get some improvement in render time from that, but it's still bad. For lag spikes, make sure you don't have something like Github running in the background. I'll experiment with Precache, but I think that would only help on first load of the model, not each successive spawn. - AFA (22 Apr 2021) > No, this happens every time, even when only GZDoom is opened. For me it's always some large model (I set all distances to 512 for testing the matter) that pops up in the view after a lag spike, e. g. the one which stands near the entrance to the opera house. As for precache, the lag spikes do not seem to appear in previously visited areas, I think the bottleneck here is either loading from HDD or unpacking the pk3 on the fly (I am running the game from an .ipk3, not from a directory). When a model respawns, the game would fetch its data directly from RAM instead of extracting the archive, and there should be no lag anymore (at least, this is my theory, it seems to hold on my machine). Also, have you noticed that on C3M5_C there is a lag spike near the beginning when the SS MP40 guard near the red door gives the player a Nazi salute? After you reload the map, it disappears (the sprites/"Herr Hauptmann!" sound would have been loaded into RAM). --N00b, 23 Apr 2021 > I get zero change in performance even with every actor precached... But I also (usually) don't get lag when I re-visit areas, either. Anyone else seeing this? - AFA (23 Apr 2021) - [x] It is possible to postpone going to C3M0_A at least after finishing C3M2. Not sure if it is desirable, some INTERMAP scripts could break (have not tested it yet), and you can also freely get a minesweeper and a repair kit which allow to circumvent some areas in C3M0_A. > Repair kits have been fixed and we can live with the minesweeper thing, but idk if INTERMAP gets broken somehow. --Ozy81 > I suspected that you could have visited C3M2 two times this way, checked it right now, this is not the case. Everything seems to work correctly. --N00b, 22 Apr 2021

Create ESS API socket listener path if it does not exist The problem occurs when the node got rebooted and anax failed to restart with the following error: ```` Jan 31 22:43:39 bp21 anax[8420]: I0131 22:43:39.301716 8420 authenticate.go:24] ESS: Authenticator Starting Jan 31 22:43:39 bp21 anax[8420]: E0131 22:43:39.309832 8420 resource_manager.go:149] Resource Manager: ESS Start error: Failed to setup Unix Socket listening. Error: listen unix /var/run/horizon/essapi.sock: bind: no such file or directory ```` This is because the ESS socket file is located at `/var/run/horizon/essapi.sock`. However everything under `var/run` got wiped out during reboot. After the discussion with a group of developers, we found there are other problems for ESS API socket mapping. The following is a list of to do's. - [x] Create the base directory for essapi.sock at anax start up. This can be the anax startup script or anax itself. ( _Added creation of the path in anax before starting ESS_) - [x] Test reboot and reregister case for native agent - [x] Test reboot and agent container restart for the anax in container case. (_Tested on Mac, socat does not survive reboot_) - [x] Test multiple agent container case

qucs commandline operations (schematics -> netlist conversion) require X server As of version 0.0.19 (probably also previous builds) using `qucs` from commandline under Linux seems to require X server to be present. Since `qucsconv` does not support converting schematics (.sch) to netlists (or at least said feature is not mentioned in the Wiki) it renders the program unusable under environments where X server is unavailable. In case it's as simple as me misusing qucs, that's what I am trying to launch: ``` qucs -n -i test_pwm.sch -o test_pwm.net qucsator -i test_pwm.net -o test_pwm.output ``` Executing these commands where X server is available results in correct behaviour ("try to load schematic..." etc. output to stdout, files are created and they seem to contain valid data), whereas otherwise the only feedback I'm receiving is ``` Warning: qucs: cannot connect to X server ``` A quick sweep around the source code shows that a `QApplication` is instantiated in all cases, even when using qucs purely from commandline - which seems like an awkward design choice. EDIT: Issue still persists on the latest code from `develop` branch. Cheers!

state of ${ shared; } command substitutions leaks out of parent subshells A command substitution of `${ `*this form*`; }` is documented to share its state with the parent shell environment. However, when it is run within a virtual/non-forked subshell, variables that are not already local to that subshell will leak out of it into the grandparent state. Reproducer: ``` $ ksh -c '( v=${ bug=BAD; } ); echo "$bug"' BAD ``` If the variable pre-exists in the subshell, the bug does not occur: ``` $ ksh -c '( bug=BAD1; v=${ bug=BAD2; } ); echo "$bug"' ``` (empty line, as expected) This bug exists on 93u+ 2012-08-01 as well as ksh2020. Presumably it has always existed on ksh93 ever since it introduced this form of command substitution.

ApiController generator fails to handle parameters in controller base route declaration Hey Kai, seems like I discovered bit of an edge case bug in the ApiController service generator ;-D It only happens when I'm trying to put a **parameter on every endpoint route** for a specific controller.... If I move the parameter to every endpoint route, the generator builds the correct routes. ``` [Route("api/devices/{deviceUid}")] [GenerateAngularService(Generator.GeneratorServiceOutputPath, Generator.GeneratorModelPath, "{0}ApiService")] [GenerateIgnoreGeneric(typeof(Response<>))] public class DeviceController : ControllerBase .... ``` Any endpoint on this controller will be generated to something like: ``` this.http.get<boolean>(this.serviceUrl + "/api/devices/{deviceUid}/data" + "?deviceUid=" + this.convertAny(deviceUid), httpOptions).subscribe((result) => {... ``` which correctly should be: ``` this.http.get<boolean>(this.serviceUrl + "/api/devices/" + deviceUid + "/data", httpOptions).subscribe((result) => {``` **without** the additional ```{deviceUid}```

ds-jupyter-notebook renaming to ds-jupyter-lab **Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.** `ds-jupyter-notebook` is not just a notebook but the Jupyter IDE suite where you are provided not only notebooks, but also terminals. So, I am proposing to renaming it accordingly to `ds-jupyter-lab`. **Describe the solution you'd like** To have a fitting name for what this quickstarter provides. **Describe alternatives you've considered** Keep it as is. **Additional context** If we do not proceed with a proper renaming at least to make it more clear at documentation level.

Batch processing/batch normalization for SOM **Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.** The current SOM code iterates through each point one at a time. I think there might be some speedups if we can batch this for multiple points. However, more importantly, I think we're less likely to run into problems with the normalization if we have data from multiple FOVs. 99.9% normalization from a single FOV could lead to weird results. **Describe the solution you'd like** An option to specify a bath size, both for training and running, which controls how much data is fed through the SOM at a time.

WMR Portal Active + VR-disabled Vulkan game = white screen If Windows Mixed Reality portal is open and active, but you want to play a Xenko game without VR (by not using a VR-enabled graphics compositor) -- the game rendesr a white screen to the desktop (which is the behavior when VR is enabled). VRSettings.Enabled is false and a VRDevice is not initialized when debugging the engine, and nothing shows on a VR headset... it just appears rendering doesn't work to the desktop in this specific situation. Simply closing out of Windows Mixed Reality portal (shutting down the VR headset) resolves this problem. Unsure how other VR headsets without Windows Mixed Reality portal will behave. Might just have to tell people to make sure VR is disabled until this is fixed.

Engine Plate procedural drag issue Bug Description: KSP 1.10.1 included a fix for a stock bug with drag cubes for engine plates (bug # 25712 in the KSP Bug Tracker). The fix was to add "useProceduralDragCubes = true" in the config for each engine plate, inside ModulePartVariants. Because ReStock overwrites the stock ModulePartVariants with its own information for the engine plates, but does not include useProceduralDragCubes in the new ModulePartVariants, the ReStock engine plates are still affected by the drag bug. I confirmed that an additional ModuleManager patch to add "useProceduralDragCubes = true" back in fixes the issue and restores the correct drag behaviour for engine plates. Steps to reproduce: build a craft including an engine plate, then observe that the drag occlusion numbers go to zero when switching engine plate variants or on launching. The drag debug tools also show that the parts above and below the engine plate are not occluded at all.

Comparing against the wrong base (master) commit The action compares a commit of a branch to the where it branched off master. Github seems to merge this commit with master head, so unit tests include master head and should compared against that (at least in pull_request_target). This has happened [here](https://github.com/EnricoMi/publish-unit-test-result-action/pull/82#issuecomment-774544822). Make sure to compare to the master commit that is part of the merge, not master head, as master could have moved further while the action is running. What if that commit cannot be merged into master? On which commit does GitHub actions run then?

Support for Tokio 0.3 The crate currently depends on Tokyo ^0.2, but maybe it would be beneficial to update to the new version since it's considered a [beta before 1.0](https://tokio.rs/blog/2020-10-tokio-0-3). If you try to run a program that uses both the `cloud-storage` and the `tokio 0.3` crates, you get a "thread 'main' panicked at 'not currently running on the Tokio runtime." error. For now, I can use the [tokio-compat-02](https://crates.io/crates/tokio-compat-02) crate as a workaround, and it could also be used when updating `cloud-storage` to use tokio 0.3, while its other dependencies also update themselves to use it.

extend_schema_field does not seem to accept raw dicts **Describe the bug** [The docs for extend_schema_field](https://drf-spectacular.readthedocs.io/en/latest/drf_spectacular.html#drf_spectacular.utils.extend_schema_field) state it accepts a raw dict as the `field` argument, but it does not seem to be the case. **To Reproduce** Create a custom field, extend it with a `dict`, and use the field somewhere: ```python from drf_spectacular.utils import extend_schema_field @extend_schema_field({ 'oneOf': [ {'type': 'string'}, {'type': 'boolean'} ] }) class MyCustomField(serializers.Field): pass class MySerializer(serializers.Serializer): le_field = MyCustomField() ``` Generating the schema then causes two warnings: ``` Warning #0: unable to extract field metadata from field "{'oneOf': [{'type': 'string'}, {'type': 'boolean'}]}" because it appears to be neither a Field nor a Serializer. Proper handling may require an Extension or @extend_serializer_field. Skipping metadata extraction. Warning #1: could not resolve serializer field "{'oneOf': [{'type': 'string'}, {'type': 'boolean'}]}". defaulting to "string" ``` Also note that the first warning mentions `extend_serializer_field` when the decorator is now called `extend_schema_field`. **Expected behavior** The schema should be overriden with the dict as it is, just like what `OpenApiParameter`'s `type` does. This causes fields that could use `allOf`, `oneOf` or other constructs that cannot be reproduced by a custom serializer or a `PolymorphicProxySerializer` require a separate field extension.

[BUG] High CPU / Latency when adding/removing large number of routes Hi Everyone, We are working on a reported behavior where a Linux VM is being used as a gateway and routes are being added/removed dynamically and in some cases, large numbers of routes at a time. It was brought to our attention that when that happens, the waagent will spike on CPU usage and also cause a little bit of latency for a while, which sometimes last minutes until it goes back to a more stable scenario due to it processing all the routes being added. We noticed using pings and mtr that the latency on network usually was averaging 68ms between 2 VM's on different peered vnets and it went up to 117ms. Currently we are testing by using a script which allows us to add/remove large numbers of routes to make it easier: ```` import os import sys from netaddr import IPNetwork action = sys.argv[1] num = int(sys.argv[2]) network = IPNetwork('10.1.8.0/16') for i, cidr in enumerate(network): cmd = 'ip route {} {} dev eth0 src 10.0.2.4 metric 100'.format(action, cidr) os.system(cmd) if i > num: print('Num of routes {}'.format(num)) break ````` Where you can use: ````` python routes.py add 1000 or python routes.py del 1000 ````` That would either add or remove the number of routes specified in the command. This can be reproduced easily on any distribution, for our case, it was tested with Ubuntu 18.04 LTS and the latest waagent and kernel: ```` WALinuxAgent-2.2.45 running on ubuntu 18.04 Python: 3.6.9 Goal state agent: 2.2.53 Both VM's are at kernel version: 5.4.0-1031-azure ```` It does look that this is being caused by the waagent having to process the amount of routes being added. The main ask here is to see if there is any way to make that less aggressive or optimize the logic so it doesn't introduce the latency observed. As far as CPU usage, we can see if dipping in and out everytime we restart the waagent since it will process that again, for example, this is a snapshot of mpstat while restart the waagent: ![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/16481759/102543909-ddfc2d80-4068-11eb-914d-0e0da4fc3463.png) This is the output from MTR after running it for a while. The high latency was observed for a while and that is the current problem with the report since it can affect the connectivity in these cases where routes are being added/removed dynamically. The issue is also not present with the waagent stopped (since there is no process on the routes). ![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/16481759/102544133-316e7b80-4069-11eb-82fe-5d061fb07526.png) Another point that might be interesting to explore, would be to possibly pin our process to one CPU only too, not sure what that would buy but at least other cores would be still free. This behavior is also noticed on larger VM's, in my test I used Standard DS2_V3 VMs. Thank you, -Marco

Encoded data is encoded once more With `input.decode_cf` set to false (the default), nc2zarr loads encoded data into memory. The first time a variable is written, its encoded data is correctly written as-is even if it contains the `scaling_factor` or `add_offset` attributes. But when nc2zarr (actually the `xarray.to_zarr()` method) attempts to append a new time step to existing data, it uses the existing variable encoding information to encode the already encoded data before writing it. This leads to corrupt datasets if `scaling_factor` or `add_offset` attributes are used. The actual issue has its root cause in `xarray.to_zarr()` method that behaves inconsistently. A new `encode_cf` keyword argument would also help.
